Biography

2024: Returning running back … preseason All-ACC selection by Athlon Sports (3rd team) … in 35 career games (1 start), has rushed 200 times for 1,194 yards (5.97) with 11 TDs and recorded 11 receptions for 145 yards (13.18) ... carded a career-high 16 carries for 110 yards with one TD against Florida State in 2023 … has one multi-scoring game after two rushing scores against Boston College in 2022 ... logged 30+ rushing yards on 17 occasions ... earned a career-long 59-yard TD scamper against Virginia in 2022 ... registered 2+ receptions against Miami in 2022 … accumulated a career-high 32 yards receiving versus UCF in the 2022 Military Bowl … has 16 plays (13 rushing and 3 receiving) that covered 20+ yards, including six for a TD (all rushing) ... has totaled 66 points from 11 rushing TDs ... has played 702 career snaps … joined Jordan Waters in 2023 to become the fourth pair of running backs to eclipse the 600-yard mark on the ground during the same season … currently ranks tied for sixth all-time in program history for most rushing TDs of 20+ yards … heading into 2024, ranks 41st in program lore for career rushing yards.

2023: Played in all 13 games, making one start against North Carolina ... compiled 116 rushes for 674 yards (5.81) with six TDs and four receptions for 64 yards (16.00) ... placed second on the team in rushing attempts, rushing yards and rushing TDs, while sitting fourth in scoring with 36 points from six TDs ... rushed 4+ times in 12 contests and 10+ times on six occasions ... posted a season-best 16 carries against Florida State … broke free for a year-best 58-yard TD scamper against Virginia ... carded 30+ rushing yards on nine occasion and 100+ rushing yards twice against Florida State (110 yards) and Virginia (100) … notched rushing scores against Clemson, Florida State, Lafayette, Pittsburgh, Virginia and Wake Forest … recorded one reception on four occasions against Clemson, Lafayette, Notre Dame and Wake Forest … tallied a year-long 28-yard reception versus Clemson ... had eight plays (7 rushing & 1 receiving) covering 20+ yards, including four for a TD (all rushing) ... on the field for 324 snaps … paired with RB Jordan Waters (819) to form the fourth running backs duo in program lore to eclipse the 600-yard mark on the ground during the same season … also teamed with Waters (12) to form the 32nd duo in program history to each total 5+ rushing TDs in a campaign ... finished the year ranked tied for fourth in rushing TDs of 20+ yards and 12th in highest average per rushing attempt … on Duke’s bowl game charts, Birmingham Bowl totals rank 15th in rushing yards (73).

2022: Played in 11 games, missing the Kansas and Pittsburgh contests ... rushed 79 times for 508 yards (6.43) with five TDs ... placed third on the team in rushing yards and TDs ... added seven receptions for 81 yards (11.57) ... rushed 4+ times in nine contests and 10+ times in three games ... posted a season-best 15 carries for 82 yards with two TDs against Boston College … broke free for a year-best 59-yard TD scamper against Virginia ... carded 30+ rushing yards on eight occasions ... recorded a season-best two receptions against Miami and a year-long 32-yard reception versus UCF in the Military Bowl ... season-long reception against UCF was tied for the 12th longest in Duke bowl game history … had eight plays (6 rushing & 2 receiving) covering 20+ yards, including two for a TD (both rushing) … joined QB Riley Leonard (699), RB Jordan Waters (566), and RB Jaylen Coleman (480) to form the first quartet in Duke history to post 400+ rushing yards in a single season ... coupled with Leonard (13), Waters (8), and Coleman (4) to form the first foursome in Blue Devil history to compile 4+ rushing TDs in a single season ... finished sixth all-time on Duke’s single-season chart for highest average per rushing attempt ... on the field for 204 snaps.

2021: Played in 11 games, missing action against Miami … totaled five rushes for 12 yards (2.40) … recorded a season-high four carries for nine yards at Virginia … on the field for 174 snaps, primarily on special teams.

PRIOR TO DUKE: Lettered four years at Suwannee under coach Kyler Hall ... three-star prospect by ESPN.com and 247Sports.com ... charted as the No. 80 athlete in the nation by 247Sports.com ... rushed 351 times for 2,591 yards and 49 TDs in prep career … added 38 receptions for 611 yards with eight TDs … during senior season, accumulated 1,269 passing yards with 16 TDs … guided Suwanee to an 8-3 mark and a second-round berth in the Class 5A playoffs in 2021 ... named Lake City Reporter’s Offensive Player of the Year ... also competed in weight lifting, was a state qualifier in the 183 weight class, and helped the team to back-to-back district and regional titles.

PERSONAL: Born July 19, 2003 ... double majoring in sociology and African & African American studies ... son of Anthony Lee and Janet Moore … cousin, John Perry, lettered four years in football at Tusculum University (2010-11-12-13).
